---------------------------------------------------------------------------
- README file for aperta reference applicaion                              -
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

Description
-----------
This README was intended to explain the use of aperta reference application

-> Aperta reference applications are intended to show how to configure aperta using BCM API. 
This reference application works only under broadcom testing environment.

-> The PHY ID (consecutive) used in the application is the MDIO bus address used for the
chip setup (defined in aperta_common.h).
 
-> User may not get desired outcome if they try to re-use reference application as-is. 

-> Please contact broadcom AE's for further queries on aperta reference application.

-> MDIO WRITE/READ API Trace Enable:
    - Enable "BCM_PLP_MDIO_TRACE_WRITE_ENABLE" compilation flag in "Makefile" to print
      the MDIO Write API data/address transactions.

      Ex: MDIO Write Trace is enabled in the Makefile
      ADD_FLAGS += -DBCM_PLP_MDIO_TRACE_WRITE_ENABLE

    - Enable "BCM_PLP_MDIO_TRACE_READ_ENABLE" compilation flag in "Makefile" to print
      the MDIO Read API data/address transactions.

      Ex: MDIO Read Trace is enabled in the Makefile
      ADD_FLAGS += -DBCM_PLP_MDIO_TRACE_READ_ENABLE

      - By default these options are disabled in the Makefile.
      Ex: MDIO Write/Read Trace is disabled.
      #ADD_FLAGS += -DBCM_PLP_MDIO_TRACE_WRITE_ENABLE
      #ADD_FLAGS += -DBCM_PLP_MDIO_TRACE_READ_ENABLE

      Note: INITIALIZE/MEMSET EVERY FUNCTION PARAMETERS TO zero,
      TO AVOID FUTURE COMPATIBILITY ISSUES WITH THE DRIVER.
